<span id="Introduction"></span>
==Einleitung==

Die Anleitung '''Kegelräder''' beschreibt, wie man die erforderlichen Daten zusammentragt, um ein Paar Kegelräder mit dem Werkzeug [[Image:FCGear_BevelGear.svg|16px]] [[FCGear_BevelGear/de|Kegelrad]] des Arbeitsbereichs [[Image:FCGear_workbench_icon.svg|16px]] [[FCGear_Workbench/de|FCGear]] in einem [[Image:Workbench PartDesign.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Workbench|PartDesign]]-Umfeld zu erstellen.

[[Image:BevelGears_Example00.png|300px]]

{{Caption|Ein Paar ineinandergreifender Kegelräder}}

Ein Kegelrad kann entweder vom Teilkreis aus oder von der virtuellen Spitze her aufgebaut werden; das hängt von seiner Einstellung '''reset_origin''' ab. In späteren Schritten dieser Anleitung müssen wir das Kegelrad skalieren ohne die Spitze zu verschieben und daher werden wir diese Eigenschaft deaktivieren. 

<span id="Requirements"></span>
==Voraussetzungen==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The [[Image:FCGear_BevelGear.svg|16px]] [[FCGear_BevelGear|BevelGear]] tool creates a bevel gear for perpendicular axes and a ratio of 1 : 1 by default. For other axis angles and different rations we need to determine the proper pitch cone angle for both of the paired bevel gears. In addition we have adjust basic values and derive the pitch diameters.
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Basic Values===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Assumed that we tortured our brain to consider available space, loads, ratio, and angle between the axes and now found these basic values:
: Module: m = 2 mm
: Ratio: 5 : 3
: Axis angle: 60°
</div> 

<span id="Number_of_Teeth"></span>
===Zähnezahl===

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
To not overload our CPUs we will set the number of teeth (z) of the smaller gear to only {{Value|9}} and so the number of teeth of the larger one is set to {{Value|15}} (15 : 9 equals 5 : 3).
: z1 = 15 (for '''bevel gear 1''')
: z2 = 9 (for '''bevel gear 2''')
</div>

<span id="Pitch_Diameter"></span>
===Teilkreisdurchmesser===

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Now we can calculate the pitch diameters (d):
: d1 = z1 * m = 15 * 2 mm = 30 mm
: d2 = z2 * m = 9 * 2 mm = 18 mm
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Cone Angles===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Now it is FreeCAD's turn to find the pitch cone angles (δ):
# Create a [[Image:Std_New.svg|16px]] [[Std_New|new document]].
# Create a [[Image:PartDesign_Body.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Body|Body]] ('''Body''').
# Create a [[Image:Sketcher_NewSketch.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_NewSketch|Sketch]].
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
We use the sketch to draft 2 connected triangles with their symmetry axes perpendicular to the sides representing the pitch diameters. Apart from several hidden coincident and symmetry constraints we use two length constraints for the pitch diameters and an angle constraint for the axis angle to fully constrain the sketch, then we are able to use two reference constraints to obtain both pitch cone angles (and leave the sketch):
</div>

[[Image:BevelGears_Example01.png|300px]]

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Caption|Red: Constrained axis angle, and both pitch diameters.<br>Blue: Resulting pitch cone angles}}
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
We now have the pitch cone angles:
: δ1 = 38,21°
: δ2 = 21,79°
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Raw Gears==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
We are ready to create our pair of bevel gears
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Bevel Gear 1===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
#Create a new [[Image:PartDesign_Body.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Body|PartDesign Body]] ('''Body001''').
# Invoke the [[Image:FCGear_BevelGear.svg|16px]] [[FCGear_BevelGear|BevelGear]] command.
# A bevel gear ('''BevelGear''') is created immediately with its pitch diameter side touching the origin, and awaiting adjustment.
# In the [[Property_View|Property View]] adjust these properties of the bevel gear:
## Set the {{PropertyData|module}} property to {{Value|2 mm}}.
## Set the {{PropertyData|num_teeth}} property to {{Value|15}}.
## Set the {{PropertyData|pitch_angle}} property to {{Value|38,21°}} (two decimal places should be more than enough).
## Uncheck the {{PropertyData|reset_origin}} property to place the bevel gear's virtual tip on the origin (this will turn the bevel gear upside down).
# Use [[Image:Std_TransformManip.svg|16px]] [[Std_TransformManip|Transform]] to swivel the bevel gear around the origin so that its face on the pitch circle side is parallel to the horizontal line of the sketch representing the same pitch circle of the larger gear (if we filled in the values properly the line should be coplanar with the face).
</div>

[[Image:BevelGears_Example02.png|300px]]

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Caption|Bevel gear 1 properly positioned}}
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Bevel Gear 2===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Create another new [[Image:PartDesign_Body.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Body|PartDesign Body]] ('''Body002''').
# Invoke the [[Image:FCGear_BevelGear.svg|24px]] [[FCGear_BevelGear|BevelGear]] command.
# A bevel gear ('''BevelGear002''') is created.
# In the [[Property_View|Property View]] adjust these properties of the bevel gear:
## Set the {{PropertyData|module}} property to {{Value|2 mm}}.
## Set the {{PropertyData|num_teeth}} property to {{Value|9}}.
## Set the {{PropertyData|pitch_angle}} property to {{Value|21,79°}}.
## Uncheck the {{PropertyData|reset_origin}} property to place the bevel gear's virtual tip on the origin (this will turn the bevel gear upside down).
# Use [[Image:Std_TransformManip.svg|24px]] [[Std_TransformManip|Transform]] to swivel the bevel gear around the origin so that its face on the pitch circle side is parallel to the oblique line of the sketch representing the same pitch circle of the smaller gear (if we filled in the values properly the line should again be coplanar with the face).
</div>

[[Image:BevelGears_Example03.png|300px]]

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Caption|Bevel gear 2 properly positioned}}
